Honest Digbara, a notorious criminal in Rivers State popularly known as Bobisky, has been killed by the police in the state, Daily Times reports. The criminal, who had been tied to several organised crimes in the state including armed robbery and kidnapping, had been tailed by police for a good while. READ ALSO: Rivers State government, IG of Police, SARS Commander tangle in accusations, denials of criminal activities The Rivers State government even declared Bobisky wanted with a bounty of â‚¦30 million offered to whoever could assist in his eventual arrest. He is said to have been killed on Saturday, sparking wild jubilation and excitement among residents of the state. Digbara was reportedly apprehended during a sting operation by the Rivers Police Command in Korokoro community in Tai Local Government Area of the state.